1. Install the virtualEnv Package for Python:
    - Open command prompt
    - type: pip install virtualenv
    - cd your project directory
    - type: virtualenv venv --python=python3.8  (or any other version of python you have)

2. Project Structure:
    - Create a Blog folder (for example)
    - Create a new Python project called "Tests" under Blog
    - Create 3 python files as shown in structure:
        Blog (Folder)
            Tests (Folder)
            app.py       (Python file)
            blog.py      (Python file)
            post.py      (Python file)

    - Create a new Python Package called "Unit" under tests

